totemic.entry.melody=Melody
totemic.page.melody0=Â§4MelodyÂ§0 is a magical power released from Â§4InstrumentsÂ§0 that have been played. Each Â§1InstrumentÂ§0 has a Â§4Melody ThresholdÂ§0, meaning that only a certain amount Â§4MelodyÂ§0 can be released from one Â§4InstrumentÂ§0 for a specific effect.<br>Maybe in the future this Â§4MelodyÂ§0 will have functions with other things in the world.

totemic.entry.cedarTree=The Red Cedar tree
totemic.page.cedarTree0=The Â§1Red Cedar TreeÂ§0 is a tree that naturally has capabilities for Totemic purposes. It can be obtained by infusing mundane saplings with musical energy in the Â§4Rite of Spring CeremonyÂ§0. Â§1Red Cedar WoodÂ§0 has the same properties and crafting applications as standard wood. In addition, a Â§4Bark StripperÂ§0 is able to remove its bark to make more efficient uses of its resources.
totemic.page.cedarTree1=Finally, it can be used to craft certain instruments like the Â§1Wind ChimesÂ§0 or Â§1Jingle DressÂ§0.

totemic.entry.buffaloBasic=Buffaloes
totemic.page.buffaloBasic0=The mighty Buffalo, an animal which is known across the lands for all of the resources it can grant. They are incredibly sturdy and have a very large amount of health. Hunting has left them nearly extinct, but they can still be 'created' with the Â§4Buffalo Dance CeremonyÂ§0.

totemic.entry.creatingTotems=Â§oTotem Poles
totemic.page.creatingTotems0=Creating a Â§4Totem PoleÂ§0 is a very simple thing to do. First you must create a Â§1Totem Whittling KnifeÂ§0, which is the tool used to carve out a Â§4Totem PoleÂ§0 out of any kind of wood logs. The knife can carve different patterns of Â§4Totem PolesÂ§0, which will lead to different effects. Right clicking or scrolling while sneaking will change which pattern will be carved.
totemic.page.creatingTotems1=A Totem Whittling Knife is also needed to carve out the Â§1Totem BaseÂ§0. Each Totem Pole needs one Totem Base at the bottom of the pole, and can can extend 6 meters high.<br>Totem Poles will by default give beneficial Â§4effectsÂ§0 to all nearby players. The effects depend on the carving pattern. A Totem Pole can have different carvings on different heights.

totemic.entry.totemEffects=Totem Effects
totemic.page.totemEffects0=These are the different effects you can carve on a Totem pole:<br>Â§1BatÂ§0: Negates fall damage and lets you jump further when you sneak mid-air<br>Â§1BlazeÂ§0: Gives you Fire Resistance<br>Â§1BuffaloÂ§0: Makes you mine faster
totemic.page.totemEffects1=Â§1CowÂ§0: Gives you resistance to damage, but also slows you down<br>Â§1EndermanÂ§0: Gives you night vision<br>Â§1HorseÂ§0: Gives you a speed boost<br>Â§1OcelotÂ§0: Prevents Creepers from exploding<br>Â§1PigÂ§0: Brings you good luck
totemic.page.totemEffects2=Â§1RabbitÂ§0: Gives you a jump boost<br>Â§1SpiderÂ§0: Lets you climb walls like a spider<br>Â§1SquidÂ§0: Gives you Water Breathing<br>Â§1WolfÂ§0: Gives you strength

totemic.entry.medicineBag=Medicine Bag
totemic.page.medicineBag0=The Â§1Medicine BagÂ§0 allows you to carry a Â§4Totem EffectÂ§0 with you, so you can use its benefits for a limited time without having to be near a Totem Pole.<br>Once you have crafted your Medicine Bag, Sneak+Right click it on a Totem Pole block carved with the effect you want to have. Then you can right click the bag to open it and release its effect, or to close it.
totemic.page.medicineBag1=The Medicine Bag will last for a few minutes before it depletes. To charge it, just stand near a Â§1Totem PoleÂ§0 that has your bag's effect carved into it.

totemic.entry.instruments=Â§oInstruments
totemic.page.instruments0=Instruments are a way to create Â§4MelodyÂ§0, the life of Â§1Totem PolesÂ§0. When an instrument is played, their melody will seep into a nearby Â§1Totem PolesÂ§0. Every instrument produces Â§4MelodyÂ§0 in different ways. Along that, each instrument has a different amount of Â§4MelodyÂ§0 that a Â§4CeremoniesÂ§0 may be able to accept, meaning that many different Â§4InstrumentsÂ§0 are needed for effective use.

totemic.entry.windChime=Wind Chime
totemic.page.windChime0=The Â§1Wind ChimeÂ§0 is an instrument that will wave in the wind and periodically produce Â§4MelodyÂ§0. The Â§1Wind ChimeÂ§0 cannot have any blocks below it, and must be hanging from a block above it. While the Â§1Wind ChimeÂ§0 does not create a large amount of Â§4MelodyÂ§0, it does not require any intervention by players. It is recommended that only a couple of Wind Chimes hang near a Â§1Totem PoleÂ§0 at once.
totemic.page.windChime1=It is not rare to see Â§1Wind ChimesÂ§0 hanging from the branches of leaves, there have even been rumors that it could make them create more Â§4MelodyÂ§0. When the Â§1Wind ChimeÂ§0 is playing, it will shake vigorously and create Â§1MelodyÂ§0. Because the music from the Â§1Wind ChimeÂ§0 is so easy to come by, the Â§4Melody ThresholdÂ§0 is easily reached. Hitting a Â§1Wind ChimeÂ§0 whilst Â§4SneakingÂ§0 will make it play in Â§4Selector ModeÂ§0.

totemic.entry.drum=Drum
totemic.page.drum0=The Â§1DrumÂ§0 is an instrumental block that can be played by simply bashing it with either fist. All Â§1TotemistsÂ§0 should learn the rhythm which is used when a Â§1FluteÂ§0 and a Â§1DrumÂ§0 are being played together, as it may be required for early Â§1CeremoniesÂ§0.
totemic.page.drum1=It is recommended to have a few Â§1DrumsÂ§0 around a Â§1Totem PoleÂ§0 in order to be able alternatively play them. As with most instruments, Â§4sneakingÂ§0 when playing it will allow you to select a Â§4CeremonyÂ§0.

totemic.entry.jingleDress=Jingle Dress
totemic.page.jingleDress0=The Â§1Jingle DressÂ§0. One of the most prestigious pieces of clothing available for any Â§4TotemistsÂ§0. It is a leaf dress adorned with bells. Running will create Â§4MelodyÂ§0, they say the faster you run the more it creates, and a speed potion increases it even further! Perhaps its effect could be activated by running in between Â§1DrumÂ§0 beats.
totemic.page.jingleDress1=Because the effect of this Â§1InstrumentÂ§0 is fairly passive, it does not create much Â§4MelodyÂ§0, and its Â§4Melody ThresholdÂ§0 is easily reached. Interestingly enough, it seems like the Â§4Jingle DressÂ§0 is one of the few Â§4InstrumentsÂ§0 that cannot be used as a Â§4Ceremony SelectorÂ§0.

totemic.entry.flute=Flute
totemic.page.flute0=Sometimes a Â§1FluteÂ§0 can be one of the most simple and effective instruments available. Unlike other instruments, the Â§1FluteÂ§0 simply plays music without any complication. Because of its simplicity, it is not known to be the most melodic instrument, meaning it will not create much Â§4MelodyÂ§0, and its Â§4Melody ThresholdÂ§0 will be reached easily. When Â§4sneakingÂ§0, it can be used to select a Â§4CeremonyÂ§0 for any nearby Â§4Totem PolesÂ§0.
totemic.page.flute1=The Â§1FluteÂ§0 can be infused in the Â§4Serenade for SyrinxÂ§0, giving it special properties.

totemic.entry.rattle=Rattle
totemic.page.rattle0=The Â§1Ceremonial RattleÂ§0 is an Â§4InstrumentÂ§0 which is a backbone of any more advanced Â§4CeremoniesÂ§0. The Â§1RattleÂ§0 produces Â§4MelodyÂ§0 whenever it has been shook with the hand.<br>It can be used in dual wield: if you hold the Rattle in your right hand, you can have another instrument in your left hand and play both at the same time.
totemic.page.rattle1=Like all Â§4InstrumentsÂ§0, it can be played while Â§4sneakingÂ§0 so as to activate Â§4CeremoniesÂ§0.

totemic.entry.eagleBoneWhistle=Eagle-Bone Whistle
totemic.page.eagleBoneWhistle0=The Â§1Eagle-Bone WhistleÂ§0 is made from the bones of a Â§4Bald EagleÂ§0, and as such it is very powerful. It is a necessity for more advanced Â§4CeremoniesÂ§0, and is actually considered more of a ceremonial object than an Â§4InstrumentÂ§0.

totemic.entry.netherPipe=Netherumbrian Pipes
totemic.page.netherPipe0=The Â§1Netherumbrian PipesÂ§0 are one of the most curious instruments of them all. Although a truly vile creation, it has many uses for a Totemist. Charging it up like you would a bow makes its bellows draw in air, and after releasing all of its fumes, the Â§1Netherumbrian PipesÂ§0 will drain the life of all nearby crops. After draining their life, it will release a large amount of Â§4MelodyÂ§0. What's interesting about these set of is that they will give
totemic.page.netherPipe1=off their maximum amount of music within a few plays. Do not take that lightly however, as each play creates several times more music than any other instrument. After crafting, an activation is required. To do this, simply take damage from wither effects with the Â§1Netherumbrian PipesÂ§0 in hand. Interestingly enough, it seems to prefer the life essence of Nether Wart.
