totemic.entry.basicsCeremonies=Â§oBasics of Ceremonies
totemic.page.basicsCeremonies0=Â§4CeremoniesÂ§0 are a way for a Totemist to gather strength over a period of time through the power of Â§4MelodyÂ§0 to release a central burst of energy on both players and the nearby world. The center of a Ceremony is a Â§1Totem BaseÂ§0 and it also is where the effects of a Ceremony are released from. Ceremonies are powered by the Â§4MelodyÂ§0 that is released from Â§4InstrumentsÂ§0 when they are played.
totemic.page.basicsCeremonies1=There are two main points in a Ceremony, the first being Â§4SelectionÂ§0, and the second being the Â§4Ceremony EffectsÂ§0.

totemic.entry.selectingCeremonies=Â§oSelecting Ceremonies
totemic.page.selectingCeremonies0=In order to select which Â§4CeremonyÂ§0 you wish to activate, a specific task must be complete. Any Â§4InstrumentsÂ§0 played whilst Â§4SneakingÂ§0 will play in their Â§4Selector ModeÂ§0, and will not release any Â§4MelodyÂ§0 as they would normally. A combination of two Â§4InstrumentsÂ§0 in Â§4Selector ModeÂ§0 will start a Ceremony depending on which were played. For example, using the Â§1FluteÂ§0 in selector mode twice will activate the Â§4Serenade of the DepthsÂ§0.

totemic.entry.performingCeremonies=Â§oPerforming Ceremonies
totemic.page.performingCeremonies0=Once a Â§4CeremonyÂ§0 has been selected, the Â§4startupÂ§0 will initiate. While it is in this stage, the Â§1Totem PoleÂ§0 will accept any played Â§1MelodyÂ§0 and store it. In order for a Ceremony effect to activate, a certain amount of Â§4MelodyÂ§0 is required depending on how difficult the Ceremony is. This difficulty is represented by how many â™ª there are in its entry in this book. When the Â§4Melody RequirementÂ§0 for the Ceremony is reached, it will activate.
totemic.page.performingCeremonies1=Each Â§4InstrumentÂ§0 can only be played up to a certain point, meaning a Ceremony could not be played with just one Â§4InstrumentÂ§0. This is known as the Â§4Melody ThresholdÂ§0. Any smoke that emits from the Â§1Totem BaseÂ§0 will signify that the most recently played Â§4InstrumentÂ§0 has reached its Â§4Melody ThresholdÂ§0 for that Ceremony, and the user should stop using that specific Â§4InstrumentÂ§0 for the rest of the Ceremony.
totemic.page.performingCeremonies2=Additionally, there is a limited amount of time to complete a Ceremony, meaning playing speed is important. After you have created enough Â§4MelodyÂ§0, the Ceremony will begin performing its effects. Some Ceremonies have instant effects, others will last over a certain amount of time after the effect initially starts. It should be noted that the effects can only pertain for a certain amount of time, and will stop after that time has elapsed.
totemic.page.performingCeremonies3=Finally, there should be care taken with the timing between playing Â§4InstrumentsÂ§0, in order to complete a Ceremony efficiently, a rhythm between instruments may be important. Because of that, it is recommended that a Â§4TotemistÂ§0 spends some time getting used to the rhythms of certain Â§4InstrumentsÂ§0.

totemic.entry.ceremonyTips=Â§oTips for Ceremonies
totemic.page.ceremonyTips0=â€¢ After you selected a Ceremony, you need to Â§4stop sneakingÂ§0 so that your music counts for the Ceremony.<br>â€¢ If you see white smoke coming from the Totem Pole after playing an instrument, its Â§4Melody ThresholdÂ§0 is reached and you should stop playing it.<br>â€¢ Â§4Wind ChimesÂ§0 play at somewhat regular intervals. Try to time your Ceremony around them.
totemic.page.ceremonyTips1=â€¢ More Instruments of the same kind usually don't help that much. Try getting more Â§4unique InstrumentsÂ§0 if you can.<br>â€¢ That said, it can be helpful to have two Â§4DrumsÂ§0 and two or three Â§4Wind ChimesÂ§0.<br>â€¢ Try holding your Flute in the Â§4left handÂ§0 and your Rattle in the Â§4right handÂ§0 to play both at once.
totemic.page.ceremonyTips2=â€¢ If you want to cancel a Ceremony, e.g. when you made a wrong selection, you can Â§4left-clickÂ§0 your Totemic Staff on the Totem Base.<br>â€¢ The time you have available to complete a Ceremony changes with Â§4game difficultyÂ§0.

